51.1	Shropshire	Shropshire	Shropshire ( or ; alternatively Salop; abbreviated, in print only, Shrops) is a county in the West Midlands region of England. It borders Wales to the west, Cheshire to the north, Staffordshire to the east, Worcestershire to the south-east and Herefordshire to the south. A unitary authority was created on 1 April 2009, taking over from the previous county council and 5 district councils, and covers most of the county. The borough of Telford and Wrekin, included in Shropshire for ceremonial purposes, has been a separate unitary authority since 1998.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/County_Flag_of_Shropshire.png/160px-County_Flag_of_Shropshire.png
